SIMPLE: filter
RECORDS: 4

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Filter
<hw>Fil"ter</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F. <ets>filtre</ets>,
the same word as <ets>feutre</ets> felt, LL. <ets>filtrum</ets>,
<ets>feltrum</ets>, felt, fulled wool, this being used for straining
liquors. See <er>Feuter</er>.]</ety> <def>Any porous substance, as
cloth, paper, sand, or charcoal, through which water or other liquid may
passed to cleanse it from the solid or impure matter held in suspension;
a chamber or device containing such substance; a strainer; also, a
similar device for purifying air.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Filter bed</b></col>, <cd>a pond, the bottom of which is
a filter composed of sand gravel.</cd> -- <col><b>Filter
gallery</b></col>, <cd>an underground gallery or tunnel, alongside of a
stream, to collect the water that filters through the intervening sand
and gravel; -- called also <altname>infiltration
gallery</altname>.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Filter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Filter
<hw>Fil"ter</hw>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. & p. p.</pos>
<conjf>Filtered</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb. n.</pos>
<conjf>Filtering</conjf>]</vmorph> <ety>[Cf. F. <ets>filter</ets>. See
<er>Filter</er>, <pos>n.</pos>, and cf. <er>Filtrate</er>.]</ety>
<def>To purify or defecate, as water or other liquid, by causing it to
pass through a filter.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><mcol><col><b>Filtering paper</b></col>, <it>or</it>
<col><b>Filter paper</b></col></mcol>, <cd>a porous unsized paper, for
filtering.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Filter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 3 ====
HEADWORD: Filter
<hw>Fil"ter</hw>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <def>To pass through a filter; to
percolate.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Filter</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 4 ====
HEADWORD: Filter
<hw>Fil"ter</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>Same as <er>Philter</er>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>filter-tipped</ent>⟦br⟧
